ENTRY            F0801   20251225   20260311   20260311       F107
SUBENT        F0801001   20251225   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                 12         26
TITLE      Neutron hole states in 91Mo and 93Mo studied by the
            (p,d) reaction
AUTHOR     (M.A.Moinester,G.Finkel,J.Alster,P.Martin)
INSTITUTE  (3ISLTEL) Department of Physics and Astronomy
           (2FR GRE)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,202,473,1973)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2FR GRE)
INC-SOURCE Beam currents ranged from 5 to 100 nA.
DETECTOR   The deuteron and triton reaction products were
           measured with a Goulding type deltaE-E particle
           identifying system (see REL-REF).
REL-REF    (M,,F.S.Goulding+,J,NIM,31,1,1964) - Goulding type
           deltaE-E particle identifying system
METHOD     (EDE,BCINT)
ERR-ANALYS The estimated uncertainty in the excitation energies in
           91Mo and 93Mo is about 20 keV for the low-lying states
           and 40 keV for higher-lying states.
           (ERR-1) Absolute cross section error
           (ERR-S) The statistical error is indicated by error
           flags only when the error exceeds the size of the
           circles.
ADD-RES    DWBA analysis was given.
HISTORY    (20061011C)
           (20251225A) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-1. Subents 004, 005 deleted (angle
           didn't mentioned in the article).
ENDBIB              26
COMMON               5          3
EN         EN-RSL     ERR-1      ANG-ERR-D  ERR-DIG
MEV        KEV        PER-CENT   ADEG       PER-CENT
        40.       100.        15.        0.1        0.8
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           33
SUBENT        F0801002   20251225   20260311   20260311       F107
BIB                  5         35
REACTION   (42-MO-92(P,D)42-MO-91,PAR,DA)
SAMPLE     (42-MO-92,ENR=0.976) The 92Mo target was 1 mg/cm2
           thick, enriched to 97.6%.
